SIMPLE: pithecoid
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pithecoid
<hw>Pith"e*coid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ an ape +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the genus <gen>Pithecia</gen>, or subfamily
<fam>Pithecin⟦ae⟧</fam>, which includes the saki, ouakari, and other
allied South American monkeys.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the anthropoid apes in
particular, or to the higher apes of the Old World,
collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pithful</ent>⟦br⟧
